   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.1	The extent to which the Law on Social Assistance (i) is based on rights and life cycle approach, and (ii) has implementation guidelines that clearly define institutional functions/roles. Scaling from 0-3, where: 0: right-based and life cycle approach are not included in the draft law on Social Assistance and no clear institutional functions/roles in implementation guidelines; 1: right-based and life cycle approach and clear institutional roles for implementation are included in the proposal submitted to the drafting team; 2: right-based and life cycle approach and clear institutional roles for implementation are submitted by the drafting team for further discussion; and 3: right-based and life cycle approach and clear institutional roles are included in the Law on Social Assistance and implementation guidelines
1.2	Number of new policies/schemes designed/adjusted and approved in line with the MPSAR 
2.1	Percentage of new policies and schemes that are put in implementation.
2.2	Availability of an M&amp;E system for SA policy/ scheme implementation. Scaling from 0-2, where: 0: M&amp;E system for SA policy/scheme implementation is not available, 1: M&amp;E system for SA policy/scheme implementation is prepared and shared for consultations, 2: M&amp;E system for SA policy/scheme implementation is approved and implemented.
2.3	Number of M&amp;E/oversight reports.</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2019">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.1	Rating: 0. Non-existence of the law on Social Assistance (SA). Right-based and life-cycle approach is not mentioned in SA law and guiding documents. No clear institutional functions/roles in implementation guidelines for SA law.
1.2	Rating: 0. MPSARD with defined SA policy improvements (in terms of coverage, level of benefit and targeting approach) approved by the GOVN in April 2017. However, there is no appropriate SA policies/schemes developed and approved accordingly. 
2.1	Rating: 0. No appropriate policies schemes are implemented.
2.2	Rating: 0. Non-existence of M&amp;E system for Social Assistance.
2.3	Rating: 0. Evaluation and oversights are on ad hoc basis. No M&amp;E/oversight reports based on the &#x201C;to be developed&#x201D; M&amp;E system.</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2021-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2021-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">(i) 01 set of systemic/solutions to accelerate scaling up of (1) self-registration, (2) management and (3) e-payment of social assistance system &#x2013; regular and emergency relief, produced.
(ii) 01 report on policy reform options to increase the inclusivity and responsiveness of Viet Nam&#x2019;s social assistance system, produced.
(iii) 03 consultation workshops/technical meetings on improving and finalizing the systemic/solution design to accelerate scaling up of (1) self-registration, (2) management and (3) e-payment of social assistance system &#x2013; regular and emergency relief and (4) policy reform options to increase the inclusivity and responsiveness of Viet Nam&#x2019;s social assistance system, organized. 
(iv) At least 03 training/coaching/survey events for sensemaking and solution mapping, experimentation design and implementation, conducted. 
(v) 01 action-plan for scaling up the selected solutions, developed.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">01 report on systemic/solutions to accelerate scaling up of (1) self-registration, (2) management and (3) e-payment of social assistance system &#x2013; regular and emergency relief, produced.
01 report on policy reform options to increase the inclusivity and responsiveness of Viet Nam&#x2019;s social assistance system, produced.
02 Government decisions (No. 877/QD-LDTBXH, dated 28/7/2021 on approval of Action-plan for implementation of the Master-plan on development of management information system and data base of social assistance in period 2021 &#x2013; 2025; and Decision No. 878/QD-LDTBXH, dated 28/7/2021 on approval of investment project on development of electric/online self-registration, management and improvement of integrated information system and data base of social assistance beneficiaries), issued.
03 COVID-19 rapid impact assessment reports for GoVs responses and recovery plans, produced and published/launched. 
01 draft Decree on digitalization of social assistance system, conducted. 
01 report on identified gaps and limitations of the legal framework of social protection system under the severe and long-lasting impacts of COVID-19 and designing automatically triggered mechanisms to dispatch emergency assistance via the regular social assistance system to targeted beneficiaries, drafted.
01 set of communication and training material on implementation of digital self-registration, management and e-payment of social assistance system &#x2013; regular and emergency relief.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
